title: Amazon To Open New Project Kuiper Processing Facility at NASA Kennedy Space Center
summary: Amazon has officially chosen NASA Kennedy Space Center as the location for its Project Kuiper processing facility.

title: Galactic Energy registers sixth consecutive successful launch
summary: Chinese startup Galactic Energy sent two satellites into orbit early Saturday with the company’s sixth consecutive successful launch.

title: Amazon picks Kennedy Space Center for Project Kuiper processing facility
summary: Amazon announced plans July 21 to build a satellite processing facility at NASA’s Kennedy Space Center, Florida, as it prepares to start launching 3,200 commercial Project Kuiper broadband satellites next year.

title: A promising Internet satellite is rendered useless by power supply issues
summary: "The mission of providing Internet connectivity in Alaska will be delayed."

title: El administrador de NASA viajará a Sudamérica, hablará de cooperación
summary: Como parte de una serie de reuniones con destacados funcionarios gubernamentales, el administrador de la NASA, Bill Nelson, viajará a Brasil, Argentina y Colombia a partir del lunes 24 de julio.

title: NASA Administrator to Head to South America; Discuss Space Cooperation
summary: As part of a series of meetings with key government officials, NASA Administrator Bill Nelson will travel to Brazil, Argentina, and Colombia beginning Monday, July 24.

title: NASA Begins Next Phase Of Moon to Mars Exploration Architecture Development
summary: Its been three months since NASA unveiled its "Moon to Mars" Exploration Architecture plans for human exploration and now the agency is gearing up for the crucial second phase that will focus on missions to Mars.

title: Astranis internet satellite malfunctions before beginning Alaska service, backup planned for spring
summary: Satellite internet service provider Astranis said Friday its first commercial satellite in orbit, which was intended to provide coverage to Alaska, has malfunctioned. A backup satellite is planned for the spring.

title: First Astranis satellite sidelined by post-deployment glitch
summary: The first Astranis-built satellite won’t be able to provide commercial broadband over Alaska for local telco Pacific Dataport because it can’t keep solar arrays pointed at the sun, the Californian manufacturer’s CEO John Gedmark said July 20.
